<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423435>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 6. Family Grapsidae. A) Geograpsus lividus (H. Milne Edwards, 1837) (CCDB 5076). B) Goniopsis cruentata (Latreille, 1803) (CCDB 5053). C) Pachygrapsus gracilis (de Saussure, 1857) (CCDB 5045). D) Pachygrapsus transversus (Gibbes, 1850) (CCDB 5052). Animals from Brazil, São Paulo state: Cananéia (A, C), Ilha Comprida (B), Ubatuba (D). Sex: male (A, B, D), female (C). Scale bars (mm): A—33; B—45; C—10; D—16. Photographs by R.C. Buranelli." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4423435/files/figure.png" .

